program writes "Hello Vesta" six times to the monitor.
public class VestaHello
{

  public static void main ( String[] args )
  {
    int j = 0 ;
  
    while ( j <  6 )
    {
        System.out.println( "Hello Vesta" );
        j = j + 1;
    }

  }
}
 use of a Vesta object that writes "Hello Vesta" to the monitor.
 class Vesta
{
  public void speak()
  {
    System.out.println( "Hello Vista" );
  }
}

public class VestaHello2
{

  public static void main ( String[] args )
  {
    int   j    = 0  ;
    Vesta vest = new Vesta()   ;
  
    while ( j < 6 )
    {
        vest.speak() ;
        j = j + 1;
    }

  }
}
. Now six Vesta objects are created, and each one uses its speak() method once.
class Vesta
{
  public void speak()
  {
    System.out.println( "Hello Vesta" );
  }
}

public class VestaHello3
{

  public static void main ( String[] args )
  {
    int   j = 0  ;
  
    while ( j < 6 )
    {
        Vesta vest = new Vista()   ;
        vest.speak() ;
        j = j + 1;
    }

  }
}
Again six Vesta objects are created, but now each one is a temporary, unnamed object.
class Vesta
{
  public void speak()
  {
    System.out.println( "Hello Vesta" );
  }
}

public class VestaHello4
{

  public static void main ( String[] args )
  {
    int   j    = 0  ;
  
    while ( j < 6 )
    {
        new  Vista() . speak() ;
        j = j + 1;
    }

  }
}
Now the Vesta class is modified so a Vesta object writes out its message six times:
class Vesta
{
  public void speak()
  {
    int   j    = 0  ;
  
    while ( j < 6 )
    {
        System.out.println(" Hello Vesta ");
        j = j + 1;
    }

  }
}

public class VestaHello5
{

  public static void main ( String[] args )
  {
  
    Vista vest = new Vesta() ;
 
    vest . speak ; 
  }
}
 the class definition includes a constructor that initializes the message to be printed:
 class Vesta
{
  private String message ; // The string to be printed

  // Constructor
  public Vesta( String mess )
  {
      message = mess ;  // Initialize the message
  }

  public void speak()
  {
    int   j    = 0  ;
  
    while ( j < 6 )
    {
        System.out.println( message );
        j = j + 1;
    }

  }
}

public class VestaHello6
{

  public static void main ( String[] args )
  {
  
    Vesta vest = new Vesta ( " Hello Vista " ) ;
 
    vest . speak() ; 
  }
}
